---
title: Adding Buildpacks to Cloud Foundry
---

To add a buildpack to Cloud Foundry, run:

~~~
cf create-buildpack <buildpack_name> <buildpack_path> <position> <enable|disable(optional)>
~~~

The path can be to a zip file, the URL of a zip file, or a local directory.

The position sets buildpack detection priority:

* When you push an app, Cloud Foundry runs buildpack `detect` scripts against it

* The `detect` scripts run lowest position first

Use the optional `enable` or `disable` argument to control availability of the
buildpack.

To view the available buildpacks, run `cf buildpacks`.
In the example below, we have added a python buildpack for Cloud Foundry to detect
after trying to detect the three system buildpacks.

<pre class=terminal>
$ cf buildpacks
